		<div class="c-team__content u-typo"><p style="text-align: left;">Assistant Professor of Comparative Literature and Modern Culture and Media at Brown University. Curator and documentary filmmaker. Author of books:<em> Civil Imagination: A Political Ontology of Photography</em>(2012), <em>From Palestine to Israel: A Photographic Record of Destruction and State Formation, 1947–1950</em> (2011), <em>The Civil Contract of Photography</em>(2008), <em>Death’s Showcase</em>(2001 – Winner of The Affinity Award, ICP), co-author (with Adi Ophir) of <em>The One State Condition. Occupation and Democracy in Israel/Palestine</em>, 2012), <em>This Regime Which Is Not One: Occupation and Democracy between the Sea and The River</em> (in Hebrew, 2008).</p></div>
